2.01	Shahrastani	Shahrastani	Shahrastani (1983â€“2011) was a Kentucky-bred, British-trained Thoroughbred racehorse. He won four of his seven races between 1986 and 1987, including the Epsom Derby, in which he defeated Dancing Brave, and the Irish Derby. Owned and bred by HH Aga Khan IV, he was sired by the Triple Crown winner Nijinsky and out of the mare Shademah, a half sister to the Grand Prix de Saint-Cloud winner Shakapour.	
